The paper discusses a technique for learning continuous embeddings for entities and relations in the knowledge graph, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the robustness of the knowledge graph embedding to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper deals with manipulating the plausibility of targeted facts in a knowledge graph, which is related to database management (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
